query = """
select symbol_reg
, sum(TV_usd) as tv_usd
from 
(select regexp_replace(symbol,'[empkfzc]$', '') as symbol_reg
, Round(sum(volume_opened_usd + volume_closed_usd), 0) as TV_usd
from public.orders_mt4 om
where date(om.open_time) >= '2022-04-01'
and om.cmd in (0, 1)
group by 1

union all

select regexp_replace(symbol,'[empkfzc]$', '') as symbol_reg
, Round(sum(volume_usd), 0) as TV_usd
from public.deals_mt5 dm
where date(dm.time) >= '2022-04-01'
and dm.action in (0, 1)
and dm.entry in (0, 1, 3)
group by 1) 

t1
group by 1
order by tv_usd desc
"""

def give_data_by_script(filename):
    with open(filename, 'r') as f:
        script = f.read()
    return pd.read_sql(script, con=connection)

def plot_simple_vol_trade(temp, symbol, contract_size, col):
    plt.plot(temp[col], temp['TV_usd'])
    plt.gca().yaxis.set_major_formatter(plt.matplotlib.ticker.StrMethodFormatter('{x:,.0f}'))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title(f'{symbol} - contract_size : {contract_size}')
    plt.ylabel('TV in USD')
    plt.xlabel(col)
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()
    

    
def plot_cum_tv_vol(temp, symbol, contract_size, col):
    temp['TV_sum'] = temp['TV_usd'].sum()
    temp['TV_cumulative'] = temp['TV_usd'].cumsum()
    temp['TV_part'] = (temp['TV_cumulative'] / temp['TV_sum']) * 100
    plt.plot(temp['TV_part'], temp[col])
    ymax = temp[col].max() * 0.3
    # plt.plot(temp['TV_part'], temp['spread_pip'])
    plt.xlabel('%TV')
    plt.ylabel(col)
    plt.ylim(0, ymax)
    plt.vlines(x=[50], ymin=0, ymax=ymax, linestyles = ("solid"))
    plt.vlines(x=[80], ymin=0, ymax=ymax, linestyles = ("dashed"))
    plt.vlines(x=[95], ymin=0, ymax=ymax, linestyles = ("dotted"))
    plt.legend(['cumulative_TV', 'median', '80 percentile', '95 percentile'])
    plt.title(f'{symbol} - contract_size : {contract_size}')
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

def calc_and_print(data2, col):
    for symbol, contract_size  in data2[['symbol_reg', 'contract_size']].drop_duplicates().values:
        if contract_size == 1000 and symbol != 'USOIL':
            continue
        temp = data2[
            (data2['symbol_reg'] == symbol) &
            (data2[col] != 0) & 
            (data2['contract_size'] == contract_size) 
        ].sort_values([col])

        #fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2)
        #fig.suptitle('Horizontally stacked subplots')

        plot_simple_vol_trade(temp, symbol, contract_size,  col)
        plot_cum_tv_vol(temp, symbol, contract_size, col) #'spread_pip')
        #fig.show()
